sly /slaɪ/

1. ADJ A sly look, expression, or remark shows that you know something that other people do not know or that was meant to be a secret. (眼神、表情或话语) 会意的 

例： His lips were spread in a sly smile. 他的双唇在会心的微笑中张开。 

2. slyly ADV 会意地 

例： Anna grinned slyly. 安娜会意地咧嘴笑了。 

3. ADJ If you describe someone as sly , you disapprove of them because they keep their feelings or intentions hidden and are clever at deceiving people. 虚伪的; 狡诈的 [表不满] 

例： She is devious and sly and manipulative. 她阴险、狡诈，而且爱操纵他人。

</div>

